    {
      "id": "eXgTc19oXx0QvsqA3jXLq",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1367.707357772432,
      "y": 693.4470261895292,
      "width": 937.4595336914062,
      "height": 1050,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b8H",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1731233696,
      "version": 1897,
      "versionNonce": 1363316640,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1771655156490,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "FLOWS\n\nCreate group chat\n1. client sends createGroup to server\n2. server then creates chat with chatParticipant entries\n3. includes all participants in chatParticipants (n rows for n participants)\n\nSupporting message delivery\nonline:\n1. message is sent to the chat server from client\n2. using the chatId, chat server creates the message and\n    for all the participants, add the messages into the inbox\n3. it then broadcasts the messages to the clients using the hashmap it has to the\n    respective receivers\n4. the client then acks that it has received the message\n5. message is then deleted from the inbox\n\noffline:\n1. if the receiver is offline, chat server will not broadcast it to the participant\n2. but once it comes online, it will then read through the entire inbox table for that participant\n    and send it all its messages\n3. once ack-ed, the chat server will delete from the inbox table\n\nMedia Storage\n* media (videos/ audio) is huge 100MBs, already existed chat server with message writes\n* blob storage connecting to server still passes alot of data to chat server\n* use presign URL => move the upload responsibility to client\n1. client says uploadVideo(), chat server returns it a uploadTargetUrl\n2. chat server uses its authentication to ask S3 for a presigned URL\n3. this URL has embedded authentication => allowing anyone to upload to this URL\n4. has a TTL => can only upload within this time period\n5. client uses that uploadTargetUrl, & makes a direct req to blob storage\n\n3. Client can then upload directly to S3 (PUT action)\n4. after upload succeeds, client lets the server know\n5. server then stores the objectKey in the BE\n6. when client reqs for the image again, it returns the URL where it can retrieve it from\n    (CDN or S3) by concatenating the domain + objectKey\n    i.e. cdnUrl = https://cdn.myapp.com/ + objectKey\n7. might need to add access control at the CDN for the right user\n* have a TTL in the blob storage => to not allow users to use us as a storage drive\n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "FLOWS\n\nCreate group chat\n1. client sends createGroup to server\n2. server then creates chat with chatParticipant entries\n3. includes all participants in chatParticipants (n rows for n participants)\n\nSupporting message delivery\nonline:\n1. message is sent to the chat server from client\n2. using the chatId, chat server creates the message and\n    for all the participants, add the messages into the inbox\n3. it then broadcasts the messages to the clients using the hashmap it has to the\n    respective receivers\n4. the client then acks that it has received the message\n5. message is then deleted from the inbox\n\noffline:\n1. if the receiver is offline, chat server will not broadcast it to the participant\n2. but once it comes online, it will then read through the entire inbox table for that participant\n    and send it all its messages\n3. once ack-ed, the chat server will delete from the inbox table\n\nMedia Storage\n* media (videos/ audio) is huge 100MBs, already existed chat server with message writes\n* blob storage connecting to server still passes alot of data to chat server\n* use presign URL => move the upload responsibility to client\n1. client says uploadVideo(), chat server returns it a uploadTargetUrl\n2. chat server uses its authentication to ask S3 for a presigned URL\n3. this URL has embedded authentication => allowing anyone to upload to this URL\n4. has a TTL => can only upload within this time period\n5. client uses that uploadTargetUrl, & makes a direct req to blob storage\n\n3. Client can then upload directly to S3 (PUT action)\n4. after upload succeeds, client lets the server know\n5. server then stores the objectKey in the BE\n6. when client reqs for the image again, it returns the URL where it can retrieve it from\n    (CDN or S3) by concatenating the domain + objectKey\n    i.e. cdnUrl = https://cdn.myapp.com/ + objectKey\n7. might need to add access control at the CDN for the right user\n* have a TTL in the blob storage => to not allow users to use us as a storage drive\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
