    },
    {
      "id": "sxbEWyW7lRSfHJdoqrQEX",
      "type": "rectangle",
      "x": 3371.305943281384,
      "y": 290.8792402747276,
      "width": 213.23924652222968,
      "height": 152.56551661340353,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b8y",
      "roundness": {
        "type": 3
      },
      "seed": 1021202016,
      "version": 52,
      "versionNonce": 1872303712,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1771655683190,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false
    },
    {
      "id": "ZYfVXf44dF7tmuF_JeBl2",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 4236.036143627835,
      "y": 757.4407058430987,
      "width": 793.3195190429688,
      "height": 800,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b8z",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 217912224,
      "version": 1543,
      "versionNonce": 795856480,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1771730649421,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Deep Dives 2: last seen\n\nwhile all the chat things that are happening with the WS servers,\nwe also want to support online presence\n\nsoln1\n1. when user logons (connected to the chat server) it can then send a timestamp\n    that it is logged on, in a KV store\n2. when the user logoffs (disconnect from the chat serve) it can then update\n    timestamp that it is offline\n3. users interested in the online/offline status can poll for these connections\n    at intervals\n\n*good: know exactly when the user is online/ offline\n*bad: doesnt handle frequent disconnections because of bad wifi connectivity\n\nsoln2:\n- instead of havign logoff, we only ever update last online timestamp\n- this way, when the user wants to check online status, they just lookback\n    a certain time interval(30s) of whether they were online\n\ncan we update time stamp when user makes action?\n- yea we can have the WS handler function update the presence service\n    - timestamp is marked on client side as well\n\nwhat if user is not doing anything?\n- now need a constant poll to update chat server\n\nOptimization: (client side)\n- when user has done an action & updated last seen within (30s)\n    client does not need to send the poll req\n- set a longer interval (15-30s) to not overload presence service",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Deep Dives 2: last seen\n\nwhile all the chat things that are happening with the WS servers,\nwe also want to support online presence\n\nsoln1\n1. when user logons (connected to the chat server) it can then send a timestamp\n    that it is logged on, in a KV store\n2. when the user logoffs (disconnect from the chat serve) it can then update\n    timestamp that it is offline\n3. users interested in the online/offline status can poll for these connections\n    at intervals\n\n*good: know exactly when the user is online/ offline\n*bad: doesnt handle frequent disconnections because of bad wifi connectivity\n\nsoln2:\n- instead of havign logoff, we only ever update last online timestamp\n- this way, when the user wants to check online status, they just lookback\n    a certain time interval(30s) of whether they were online\n\ncan we update time stamp when user makes action?\n- yea we can have the WS handler function update the presence service\n    - timestamp is marked on client side as well\n\nwhat if user is not doing anything?\n- now need a constant poll to update chat server\n\nOptimization: (client side)\n- when user has done an action & updated last seen within (30s)\n    client does not need to send the poll req\n- set a longer interval (15-30s) to not overload presence service",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
